main event: A silvery-white circular object was observed over Wabuska, Nevada on May 28, 1955, emitting a rumbling sound and flying at a speed greater than a jet aircraft.
interesting points: The object was observed to be flying in level flight from south to north.
The report indicates that the object could possibly have been an astronomical meteor.
The report includes no photographs of the observed object.
The report was made by a civilian witness.
The conclusion on the report form indicates that the sighting was 'possibly astronomical'.
